01:04.855 --> 01:07.066
Wow. Another one?

01:07.233 --> 01:09.693
- Yes.
- Honey?

01:09.861 --> 01:11.528
That's two today.

01:11.696 --> 01:13.405
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

01:13.573 --> 01:14.990
Honey?

01:15.158 --> 01:17.785
- Yeah?
- Waiting for the help to get that?

01:17.952 --> 01:20.704
I thought you and I were the help.

01:22.999 --> 01:25.793
- Go wash up for dinner, pumpkin.
- Okay.

01:25.960 --> 01:28.420
Mmm, smells nice.
That takeout?

01:30.048 --> 01:31.965
Mommy, look at-

01:40.100 --> 01:41.850
No!

01:42.018 --> 01:44.353
No! Ahh!

01:47.315 --> 01:52.027
Oh! No no no!

01:52.195 --> 01:54.655
You can't fight fate.

02:06.084 --> 02:09.252
We gotta get the fuck out of here.
Come on!

02:09.419 --> 02:13.882
Oh! Oh no!

02:16.928 --> 02:19.304
No!

02:19.472 --> 02:22.182
- What the fuck are you doing?
- No!

02:22.350 --> 02:24.643
Fucking stop!
Let's go!

02:24.811 --> 02:26.812
Just shut the fuck up!

02:33.194 --> 02:35.154
No!

02:42.996 --> 02:45.664
It's cool.

02:45.832 --> 02:47.332
Kids like me.

02:47.500 --> 02:50.502
No! Heather!

02:53.256 --> 02:56.049
No no!

03:51.814 --> 03:54.691
- Nick.
- Bray, what's happenin'?

03:54.859 --> 03:58.111
Willis is a rowing buddy of mine.
Where are we on his kid's case?

03:58.279 --> 03:59.696
- Willis?
- Yeah.

03:59.864 --> 04:01.615
- Oh, I kicked it down to juvie.
- Why did you do that?

04:01.783 --> 04:03.700
'Cause the case was a dog.
The kid was only 15 years old

04:03.868 --> 04:05.494
when he committed the murder.

04:05.662 --> 04:08.497
You wouldn't want to jeopardize
your 95% conviction rate.

04:08.665 --> 04:10.624
- It's actually 96%.
- 96% now?

04:10.792 --> 04:13.126
Yes. You gotta keep your books
better than that.

04:15.296 --> 04:17.673
You know, if I didn't know any better,
I'd say you were gunning for my job.

04:17.839 --> 04:19.298
You do know better.

04:19.466 --> 04:21.802
And you know that I'm aiming
much higher than that.

04:22.804 --> 04:24.513
They filed a motion to dismiss,

04:24.681 --> 04:26.515
but there's no way that
Judge Abrams honors it.

04:26.683 --> 04:27.891
I think that we can
get him on RICO.

04:28.059 --> 04:30.560
All that time and that's
what you come back with, Sarah?

04:30.728 --> 04:33.563
You might want to reevaluate
your research skills.

04:33.731 --> 04:35.565
- What else have we got?
- She's right.

04:35.733 --> 04:36.858
Mr. Rice?

04:37.026 --> 04:38.485
RICO's designed
for this kind of thing.

04:38.653 --> 04:41.071
Check out section 901 of
the Organized Crime Control Act.

04:41.239 --> 04:43.448
And you should let Sarah
try this case too.

04:43.616 --> 04:46.618
Mr. Rice, last I checked,
I was running this room.

04:46.786 --> 04:49.121
She's already done the leg-work.
I'll oversee it.

04:49.289 --> 04:51.081
I mean, Helen Keller
could try this case.

04:52.542 --> 04:55.836
Okay, Boy Wonder,
she fucks up, it's on you.

05:02.093 --> 05:03.927
Cantrell wants to see you.

05:04.095 --> 05:05.387
All right, I'll be right there.

05:05.555 --> 05:09.057
No, Nick.
He wants to see Nick.

05:10.435 --> 05:11.768
You still torturing Bringham?

05:11.936 --> 05:14.146
Let's just say I'm less impressed
with his Harvard degree than he is.

05:14.314 --> 05:15.647
Well, we can't all have
gone to Fordham.

05:15.815 --> 05:17.065
I went to Fordham night school.

05:17.233 --> 05:19.443
You know what I learned
in Fordham night school?

05:19.610 --> 05:20.902
Law school's got nothing
to do with law.

05:21.070 --> 05:23.322
Guess you skipped the course
on inter-office politics.

05:23.489 --> 05:26.241
All I need is a jury to like me.
Isn't that what you told me, Jonas?

05:26.409 --> 05:29.286
The Shelton case-
where are we?

05:29.454 --> 05:31.163
It went sideways last night-
Judge Burch.

05:31.331 --> 05:32.706
Ahh.

05:32.874 --> 05:34.666
Bad news. What now?

05:34.834 --> 05:37.544
- Let's make the deal.
- They killed a little girl, Nick.

05:37.712 --> 05:40.589
- It's an imperfect system.
- And we its imperfect servants.

05:40.757 --> 05:44.343
- However you could win this case.
- No, can't take that chance.

05:44.510 --> 05:47.137
Some justice is better
than no justice at all.

05:47.305 --> 05:49.306
You need to tell the husband.

05:49.474 --> 05:51.683
Okay.
That's part of my job.

05:51.851 --> 05:54.811
Good, because he's waiting
for you right now.

05:54.979 --> 05:56.646
What?

06:05.948 --> 06:08.825
- How are you doing?
- Good. How are you doing?

06:08.993 --> 06:11.578
Good. Sit. Sit.

06:11.746 --> 06:14.247
Well, I didn't hear back from you

06:14.415 --> 06:17.584
and made some notes
on the case.

06:17.752 --> 06:20.670
I had some good ideas.

06:20.838 --> 06:22.506
Yeah, let me
take a look at it.

06:24.092 --> 06:25.884
Well, they're just-

06:29.889 --> 06:33.517
I was gonna talk to you
about those.

06:34.519 --> 06:36.895
Do you trust me?

06:39.732 --> 06:41.942
Do you trust me, Clyde?

06:43.444 --> 06:44.694
Yeah, of course.

06:47.365 --> 06:50.575
Darby has agreed to testify
against Ames.

06:50.743 --> 06:53.328
With Darby's testimony,

06:53.496 --> 06:55.288
Ames will go
to death row.

06:59.585 --> 07:03.296
Um, what about-
what about Darby then?

07:03.464 --> 07:06.967
Darby will plead
guilty to murder.

07:07.135 --> 07:09.803
- In what degree?
- Third.

07:09.971 --> 07:12.431
He serves, what?
Five years...

07:12.598 --> 07:15.183
at best?

07:15.351 --> 07:18.228
I don't understand.
I'm sorry.

07:18.396 --> 07:22.232
We had a setback. The judge ruled
that the DNA was inadmissible.

07:22.400 --> 07:25.360
- What?
- Exclusionary rule.

07:25.528 --> 07:27.362
The opposing counsel
maneuvered it.

07:27.530 --> 07:29.698
You said this part of
the case was clear-cut.

07:29.866 --> 07:31.366
We had the blood on his shirt-

07:31.534 --> 07:33.201
It's covered under
the same rule.

07:33.369 --> 07:34.703
What about the rest of
the forensic evidence?

07:34.871 --> 07:38.498
It's not conclusive, Clyde.

07:40.501 --> 07:44.087
Okay, that's okay.
'Cause I saw- I saw their faces.

07:44.255 --> 07:47.299
I saw them do it.
I mean, he killed my little girl, Nick.

07:47.467 --> 07:50.343
You blacked out, Clyde.
Your testimony won't be reliable.

07:50.511 --> 07:53.263
You get on the stand and
the defense will tear you apart.

07:53.431 --> 07:55.849
No no, the jury's gonna
believe me though.

07:56.017 --> 07:59.144
- Because it's the truth! We can-
- We can lose.

07:59.312 --> 08:02.063
And then we'd have nothing.

08:02.231 --> 08:04.608
You will waste a whole year,
spend millions of dollars,

08:04.775 --> 08:06.693
and then both of them could
end up going free.

08:06.861 --> 08:10.405
Nick, both of them are guilty,
especially Darby!

08:10.573 --> 08:12.574
- You know that.
- It's not what you know, Clyde.

08:12.742 --> 08:15.160
It's what you can
prove in court.

08:19.040 --> 08:21.416
Please don't make a deal
with this man.

08:21.584 --> 08:23.627
Please don't make a deal with this man.
He's a monster-

08:23.794 --> 08:26.296
I'm sorry, the deal is done.
I'm sorry.

08:26.464 --> 08:28.298
I made the deal.

08:28.466 --> 08:31.426
What?
How could you do that?

08:31.594 --> 08:35.179
This is just how
the justice system works.

08:35.347 --> 08:39.433
Listen, I know you don't
think it right now,

08:39.602 --> 08:42.354
but this is a victory for us.

08:46.150 --> 08:48.276
Your office has certified
this agreement?

08:48.444 --> 08:49.694
Yes, Your Honor.

08:49.862 --> 08:53.740
Mr. Reynolds, any great insights
to share with the court today?

08:53.908 --> 08:56.910
I'm a defense attorney, Your Honor.
I don't have many of those.

09:00.414 --> 09:03.166
No, Your Honor.
No insights.

09:03.334 --> 09:06.127
Good, then I trust that we can
move forward with Mr. Ames's trial

09:06.295 --> 09:09.798
unimpeded by continuances.
A triaI date is imminent.

09:12.927 --> 09:14.761
Yeah?

09:14.929 --> 09:17.305
There's no cell phones
in my courtroom, Mr. Rice.

09:17.473 --> 09:18.807
- We've been over this-
- I'm sorry.

09:18.975 --> 09:20.100
- and over this, over this...

09:20.268 --> 09:22.936
Yeah, I had some
exigent business I-

09:23.104 --> 09:25.063
Next time it's mine.

09:29.068 --> 09:31.736
- Ah, you married?
- Excuse me?

09:31.904 --> 09:33.905
Are you married?

09:35.116 --> 09:39.035
Please fuck this up
so I can destroy you.

09:45.084 --> 09:46.876
I wish ill for no man,

09:47.044 --> 09:50.714
but Ames deserves to
suffer for what he did.

09:50.881 --> 09:54.050
I mean, you can't
fight fate, right?

10:00.057 --> 10:01.266
Nick.

10:01.434 --> 10:04.019
Once you make a decision,
live with it- move on.

10:04.186 --> 10:06.354
This job, your best asset's
a short memory.

10:06.522 --> 10:09.566
Don't beat yourself up. Too many other
people out there doing that already.

10:09.734 --> 10:10.984
Look, there's some of them
right now.

10:11.152 --> 10:14.112
Isn't this where you tell me
some type of old fable

10:14.280 --> 10:17.073
or wives' tale-

10:17.241 --> 10:19.075
All right, all right, I got one.

10:19.243 --> 10:21.161
Marcus Aurelius hired a servant
to walk behind him

10:21.329 --> 10:22.912
as he made his way through
the Roman town square.

10:23.080 --> 10:25.165
And this servant's only job

10:25.333 --> 10:28.001
was to whisper in his ear
when people praised him,

10:28.169 --> 10:31.463
"You're only a man.
You're only a man."

10:31.631 --> 10:33.048
- Okay, man?
- Okay, man.

10:33.215 --> 10:34.466
- Okay, man.
- That's some bullshit.

10:34.634 --> 10:35.634
That's good.

10:35.801 --> 10:37.093
I don't think you even know
what that story means.

10:37.261 --> 10:39.387
You're missing the point, Nick.
It doesn't matter what they say.

10:39.555 --> 10:41.056
Okay, I got this now.

10:44.101 --> 10:46.853
All right, ladies and gentlemen,
one at a time, one at a time.

10:47.021 --> 10:48.772
So you'll be seeking
the death penalty?

10:48.939 --> 10:50.940
- For Rupert Ames, we will be.
- And for Darby?

10:51.108 --> 10:53.610
He has pled guilty to murder,
but he is a cooperating witness.

10:53.778 --> 10:56.154
The DA's office has committed
all of its resources

10:56.322 --> 10:58.823
to ensure that justice
will be served.

10:58.991 --> 11:00.659
Did you make any kind of-

11:00.826 --> 11:02.577
Do you think this is
a fair sentence for Darby?

11:05.498 --> 11:09.125
I just wanted to say
thanks for being in my corner.

11:09.293 --> 11:12.295
It's nice when
the system works, right?

11:12.463 --> 11:14.589
Get away from me.

11:14.757 --> 11:17.092
Move. Move.

11:22.598 --> 11:24.349
Let's go.

11:54.714 --> 11:57.298
- Nick?
- Hey.

12:09.937 --> 12:12.105
Nuh-uh, what happened?

12:12.273 --> 12:14.524
What happened to what?

12:15.735 --> 12:17.861
What's wrong?

12:18.863 --> 12:22.198
You call my job boring. "C-"?

12:22.366 --> 12:23.908
Yes.

12:25.035 --> 12:28.163
Well...
okay now...

12:28.330 --> 12:30.206
you gonna tell me
what's wrong?

12:30.374 --> 12:33.918
Can I talk to my daughter
for a little bit?

12:34.086 --> 12:37.046
- Oh, please. No no no.
- Gonna lay down.

12:37.214 --> 12:39.549
Please?

12:39.717 --> 12:41.843
First of all,
this is your father speaking.

12:42.011 --> 12:43.720
- Yeah, she didn't know that.
- You never know.

12:43.888 --> 12:46.681
I want you to stay in there
as long as you can.

12:46.849 --> 12:49.017
'cause there's a lot
of crazy-ass people out here.

12:49.185 --> 12:50.935
Language.

12:51.103 --> 12:54.147
Your mother's a hardass, but-

12:54.315 --> 12:55.565
I'm right here.

12:55.733 --> 12:59.319
And Daddy- Daddy wants you to
come out and be Daddy's little girl.

12:59.487 --> 13:02.155
I want her to come out
'cause she's on my bladder.

13:02.323 --> 13:04.157
Ahh!

13:05.576 --> 13:07.786
Anybody seen my phone?

13:12.041 --> 13:15.502
- Hey, have you seen my phone?
- It's not strapped to your hand?

13:15.669 --> 13:17.629
No, it's not strapped to my hand.

13:17.797 --> 13:19.506
- Daddy?
- Yeah?

13:19.673 --> 13:21.132
You're not gonna have
some of my French toast?

13:21.300 --> 13:23.051
- French toast? You made French toast?
- Mm-hmm.

13:23.219 --> 13:26.095
I can't, honey.
I'm running late.

13:26.263 --> 13:27.514
Okay.

13:27.681 --> 13:30.767
All right, here- Mmm.

13:30.935 --> 13:32.560
- Mmm, that's good.
- Thank you.

13:32.728 --> 13:33.770
- You did this by yourself?
- Mm-hmm.

13:33.938 --> 13:35.647
I'm just gonna take
this whole plate to work.

13:35.815 --> 13:38.274
All right- no.

13:38.442 --> 13:40.109
You're only 10 years old?

13:40.277 --> 13:42.278
- You better than your mother.
- I heard that.

13:42.446 --> 13:45.031
Smells good in here.
Your lifeline.

13:45.199 --> 13:47.033
'Morning, baby.
Give me a kiss.

13:47.201 --> 13:50.245
Mmm! You going to your daughter's
recitaI this afternoon?

13:51.831 --> 13:55.124
Um, I thought you were gonna
order the DVDs.

13:55.292 --> 13:56.960
Video's not the same, Nick.

13:57.127 --> 14:00.129
Mom, it's okay.
Dad's got to work, I know.

14:00.297 --> 14:03.174
See? It's all right. Dad's got to work.
And what is Dad doing today?

14:03.342 --> 14:05.009
- Lock up bad guys.
- And why does he do that?

14:05.177 --> 14:06.511
- To keep us safe.
- Yeah.

14:06.679 --> 14:09.597
She understands.
'Cause he wants us to be safe.

14:09.765 --> 14:11.558
- Baby, get your cello.
- All right.

14:11.725 --> 14:13.768
- Thank you so much.
- You're welcome.

14:13.936 --> 14:16.813
- Little Julia Child.
- Mmm.

14:18.107 --> 14:20.525
You know she's
10 years old, right?

14:20.693 --> 14:21.943
- You know that?
- I know that.

14:22.111 --> 14:23.653
She doesn't understand why
you're never around.

14:23.821 --> 14:25.822
This good-guy, bad-guy stuff-
that's just talk to her.

14:25.990 --> 14:27.657
Don't do this, come on.

14:27.825 --> 14:29.534
I can't come today.

14:29.702 --> 14:31.870
You know you have not been
to one recitaI-

14:32.037 --> 14:33.621
- How many has she had?
- Enough.

14:33.789 --> 14:36.124
Okay.
Well, we'll get the video,

14:36.292 --> 14:40.420
we'll sit down and we'll
watch it together as a family.

14:40.588 --> 14:42.714
I love you.

14:42.882 --> 14:44.173
All right?

14:44.341 --> 14:46.426
- Thank you for the toast.
- Love you.

14:46.594 --> 14:47.719
- Love you too!
- Bye.

14:47.887 --> 14:49.804
Love you.

14:49.972 --> 14:51.848
Huh.

14:52.016 --> 14:54.767
- So how's Chip?
- It's Chester.

14:54.935 --> 14:56.311
What happened to Chip?
I liked Chip.

14:56.478 --> 14:58.104
There is no Chip.

14:58.272 --> 15:00.648
And now there's no Chester.
He kept calling.

15:00.816 --> 15:03.151
- Sarah, that's a good thing.
- I know, but I kept cancelling.

15:03.319 --> 15:05.153
My caseload's crazy.

15:05.321 --> 15:07.989
You know you don't have to
go to this if you don't want to.

15:08.157 --> 15:10.700
Yeah, I do. I...

15:10.868 --> 15:12.285
What's it like?

15:12.453 --> 15:14.746
No biggie.
Like watching somebody fall asleep.

15:14.914 --> 15:16.915
Except for
the not-waking-up part.

15:17.082 --> 15:18.917
Does it bother you?

15:19.084 --> 15:20.668
Not anymore.

16:05.756 --> 16:09.759
Sarah, your legs are looking
real good in those heels.

16:09.927 --> 16:13.012
Fuck off.

16:13.180 --> 16:15.807
What are you doing here, Reynolds?
Your DVD player broken?

16:15.975 --> 16:19.394
Ames has no family. I felt like
someone should be here for him.

16:19.561 --> 16:21.980
Wow, that's nice.

16:25.442 --> 16:27.151
Breathe.

16:44.336 --> 16:47.797
Rupert Ames, do you have
anything you want to say?

16:48.799 --> 16:50.925
Yeah.

16:51.093 --> 16:52.343
Uh-huh.

16:55.556 --> 16:58.141
What I did that night was wrong.

16:59.226 --> 17:02.061
I should have never been there.

17:03.188 --> 17:06.858
But I swear to God,
I didn't kill those people.

17:10.945 --> 17:13.448
The wrong man's dying here today.

17:17.118 --> 17:19.746
The wrong man's dying.

17:19.913 --> 17:21.998
That's all.

17:46.565 --> 17:48.483
Look at me.

17:49.860 --> 17:51.819
Look at me!

18:51.755 --> 18:55.716
Ahh! Fuck!

18:57.261 --> 18:59.262
Fuck!

18:59.429 --> 19:02.431
Ahh! Fuck!

19:02.599 --> 19:04.225
Oh, God.

19:05.435 --> 19:07.728
- Oh, God.
- Take her- take her out.

19:07.896 --> 19:10.106
- What the hell is going on?
- I don't know.

19:12.109 --> 19:15.403
Ahhh!

19:40.637 --> 19:43.764
What could have caused
the unexpected reaction of the inmate?

19:43.932 --> 19:45.933
We'll keep you informed.

19:46.101 --> 19:48.352
You okay? Huh?

19:48.520 --> 19:50.188
Yeah.

19:51.690 --> 19:54.150
So somebody killed the guy
you were trying to kill?

19:54.318 --> 19:55.568
What are we calling this?

19:55.736 --> 19:57.361
Clear violation of his
Eighth Amendment rights-

19:57.529 --> 19:59.322
- cruel and unusual punishment.
- Law schooI.

19:59.489 --> 20:01.699
Yeah. The machine-
how does it work on a good day?

20:01.867 --> 20:04.035
It's designed to be pain-free.

20:04.203 --> 20:06.746
It's three drugs administered
in a specific order.

20:06.914 --> 20:09.081
From this point on, we're operating
under the assumption

20:09.249 --> 20:10.666
that the machine was corrupted.

20:10.834 --> 20:13.753
We're gonna need a list of all
the people with access to that machine.

20:13.921 --> 20:16.505
- My people would not do this.
- I appreciate that, Warden,

20:16.673 --> 20:20.051
but I'm gonna need more than
a hall pass and a note from Mom.

20:20.219 --> 20:22.261
Detectives, got this off
the back of the machine.

20:22.429 --> 20:24.680
- Check it out.
- Let me see it.

20:24.848 --> 20:26.807
Right there.

20:26.975 --> 20:28.809
"Can't fight fate."

20:28.977 --> 20:30.645
What is it, Nick?

20:30.812 --> 20:33.064
During the home invasion,
Ames's accomplice

20:33.232 --> 20:35.399
said to one of the vics,
"You can't fight fate."

20:35.567 --> 20:38.861
And then he said the same thing
to me in the courtroom- prick.

20:39.863 --> 20:41.739
I can't remember his name, though.

20:41.907 --> 20:44.450
Have a look at this-
your guy?

20:44.618 --> 20:46.827
- Clarence James Darby.
- He's a cutie.

20:46.995 --> 20:48.913
- You got history with him?
- Put him away.

20:49.081 --> 20:51.791
All right, three years. That the going
rate for murder these days?

20:51.959 --> 20:53.501
There was extenuating
circumstances.

20:53.669 --> 20:56.963
The only extenuating circumstances
should be he didn't do it.

20:57.130 --> 20:59.840
Still, three years at Marion?
Fucking gladiator academy.

21:00.008 --> 21:01.801
You expect him to come back
a modeI citizen?

21:01.969 --> 21:04.387
Well, if you scholars wouldn't
contaminate the crime scenes,

21:04.554 --> 21:05.930
I could keep them
locked up longer.

21:06.098 --> 21:08.140
Authorities have refused
to comment at this point,

21:08.308 --> 21:10.268
but foul play cannot be ruled out.

21:10.435 --> 21:12.979
The prisoner had been on death row
for the past 10 years-

21:13.146 --> 21:14.605
his name, Rupert Ames.

21:14.773 --> 21:16.148
All we know at this point

21:16.316 --> 21:18.609
is what was supposed to be
a painless execution

21:18.777 --> 21:21.570
has turned into something
out of a horror film.

21:28.161 --> 21:29.870
Yeah?

21:30.038 --> 21:32.123
- Clarence Darby?
- Who's this?

21:32.291 --> 21:35.293
coke on the table,

21:35.460 --> 21:38.045
bitch on the floor- life in prison.

21:39.589 --> 21:41.674
Who the fuck is this?

21:41.842 --> 21:44.552
Look out your window,
south side.

21:45.637 --> 21:48.681
- Is this a joke? Get up!
- Ahh!

21:48.849 --> 21:51.100
South side.

21:54.021 --> 21:56.897
Motherfucker.

21:57.065 --> 21:59.859
Shit. Out of the way!

22:11.872 --> 22:14.081
- Stay down!
- You're all crazy!

22:14.249 --> 22:17.001
He's heading north!
Go go!

22:17.169 --> 22:19.962
- Damn.
- Move it, move it. Go on!

22:28.180 --> 22:30.848
- What now?
- Wipe the prints off the gun.

22:31.016 --> 22:33.142
- Get rid of it.
- No no.

22:33.310 --> 22:37.021
You fired six times, genius.
You bring any ammunition?

22:37.189 --> 22:38.898
- Lose it.
- Why are you doing this?

22:39.066 --> 22:40.733
I want to keep you
out of prison.

22:40.901 --> 22:43.652
See the abandoned factories?
Go toward them.

22:43.820 --> 22:44.820
Why?

22:44.988 --> 22:46.781
There's a cop car there
with a cop in it.

22:46.948 --> 22:48.115
What the fuck?

22:48.283 --> 22:50.910
I Tasered him, but he'll be waking up
in about 90 seconds,

22:51.078 --> 22:52.912
so you'd better move.

23:10.138 --> 23:14.058
Rise and fucking shine, bitch.
Wake the fuck up!

23:14.226 --> 23:16.060
Let's go!
Start the fucking car!

23:16.228 --> 23:17.311
- Okay!
- Do it.

23:17.479 --> 23:19.772
- Take it easy, take it-
- Come on!

23:19.940 --> 23:21.607
- Okay, let's go.
- Take it easy.

23:21.775 --> 23:24.652
Let's go!
Get in gear, shithead, now!

23:24.820 --> 23:27.154
Do it! Go go go!

23:42.671 --> 23:44.880
Get the fuck out.

23:50.303 --> 23:52.304
Let's go.

23:52.472 --> 23:54.432
Get the fuck down there!

23:54.599 --> 23:58.602
Okay. What about my wife?
My little girl?

23:58.770 --> 24:01.981
- I'll never see them again.
- Fucked up, ain't it?

24:02.149 --> 24:05.025
Oh oh oh.

24:05.193 --> 24:07.611
You don't mind if
I take this, do you?

24:07.779 --> 24:10.030
My guardian angel.

24:10.198 --> 24:12.032
I am impressed.

24:12.200 --> 24:16.245
You know why I'll never see
my wife and little girl again?

24:20.750 --> 24:23.210
'Cause you took 'em from me.

24:30.343 --> 24:32.595
You remember me?

24:34.139 --> 24:36.182
Sure you do.

24:36.349 --> 24:39.059
You came over to my house
once before.

24:39.227 --> 24:41.270
You don't remember?

24:43.190 --> 24:47.651
This tetrodotoxin...

24:48.653 --> 24:51.155
should be nicely into
your system by now.

24:51.323 --> 24:55.075
It's isolated from the liver
of a Caribbean puffer fish.

24:55.243 --> 24:58.829
So it paralyzes you,

24:58.997 --> 25:02.041
but leaves all the other
neurological functions

25:02.209 --> 25:04.084
perfectly intact.

25:04.252 --> 25:07.588
In other words, you can't move...

25:08.757 --> 25:11.300
but you feel everything.

25:12.344 --> 25:16.805
It does absolutely nothing
to blunt the pain.

25:16.973 --> 25:19.767
And you're about to
experience more of that

25:19.935 --> 25:22.311
than you could ever
fucking imagine.

25:30.362 --> 25:33.739
These are tourniquets

25:33.907 --> 25:37.993
so you don't bleed out,
'cause you may be here a while.

25:38.161 --> 25:40.246
Saline solution-

25:40.413 --> 25:42.957
that should keep us going.

25:43.124 --> 25:47.211
Clamps- nice and secure.

25:49.506 --> 25:51.257
Comfortable?

25:51.424 --> 25:54.051
You really are shaking.

25:54.219 --> 25:56.470
Sure you're all right?

25:57.681 --> 26:00.891
You'll love this-

26:01.059 --> 26:03.143
adrenaline.

26:03.311 --> 26:07.398
Now this is so you
don't pass out.

26:08.984 --> 26:11.151
There you go.

26:11.319 --> 26:14.488
How's that feel? Good?

26:16.116 --> 26:19.118
Now what we don't want
is you swallowing your tongue,

26:19.286 --> 26:21.412
so bear with me.

26:27.544 --> 26:31.297
Now this is for your penis,
but we'll get to that later.

26:33.758 --> 26:36.176
Scalpel...

26:36.344 --> 26:38.304
for your eyelids,

26:38.471 --> 26:41.307
in case you insist
on fucking shutting them.

26:43.184 --> 26:45.519
You see,

26:45.687 --> 26:49.356
I know what it feels like
to be helpless.

26:49.524 --> 26:52.943
just like when I watched you
slaughter my whole family.

26:55.238 --> 26:59.283
You know you can't
fight fate, right, Darby?

27:01.286 --> 27:02.536
Oh!

27:02.704 --> 27:07.124
And look-
I made this especially for you.

27:09.794 --> 27:13.422
You like it? Yeah,
I didn't want you to miss anything.

27:14.633 --> 27:19.094
Now you have the best
view in the house.

27:19.262 --> 27:21.138
You hear that?

27:21.306 --> 27:24.516
Your heart is beating so fast.

27:26.353 --> 27:28.646
No, me too.

27:28.813 --> 27:30.272
Okay.

27:33.276 --> 27:36.362
Now they get to
watch you suffer.

27:38.114 --> 27:41.742
They'll be the last thing
you ever see

27:41.910 --> 27:45.204
as I cut off every single one
of your fucking limbs.

27:45.372 --> 27:48.666
See, I wasn't lying

27:48.833 --> 27:52.544
when I told you that I wanted
to keep you out of prison.

27:55.590 --> 27:57.591
That was the truth.

28:33.336 --> 28:35.963
Thanks for the car.

29:01.197 --> 29:04.199
Okay, these are all
the case files on Darby.

29:04.367 --> 29:07.035
I vetted through what I could.
We have crime-scene photos-

29:07.203 --> 29:09.037
Don't need to see 'em.

29:10.165 --> 29:11.749
Okay.

29:17.338 --> 29:20.215
- What's bothering you?
- It's Darby.

29:20.383 --> 29:23.218
All the crimes he's committed
have one thing in common,

29:23.386 --> 29:25.554
and that was violence.
But yesterday at that execution,

29:25.722 --> 29:27.723
- that wasn't violence. That was-
- What?

29:27.891 --> 29:30.184
- That was intellect.
- Okay.

29:31.269 --> 29:33.520
- What are you thinking?
- I don't know.

29:33.688 --> 29:37.357
I'm just thinking maybe
we shouldn't be looking for Darby.

29:48.161 --> 29:50.078
Jesus Christ.

30:02.634 --> 30:04.384
Rice.

30:04.552 --> 30:07.471
Good news, Counselor. We found Darby.

30:07.639 --> 30:10.724
I gotta say though,
he's looked better.

30:11.893 --> 30:14.645
They found him in about 25 pieces:

30:14.813 --> 30:18.273
no legs, no arms,
eyelids were sliced off- gruesome.

30:18.441 --> 30:20.275
- Shedding tears for Darby?
- Not quite.

30:20.443 --> 30:23.445
- I see your wheels turning.
- Think motive- who has one?

30:23.613 --> 30:26.281
The husband, the father.
What do we know about him?

30:26.449 --> 30:28.200
He owned the warehouse
where they found Darby.

30:28.368 --> 30:29.701
- What else?
- He's a tinkerer-

30:29.869 --> 30:33.622
uh, little inventions, gizmos.
He holds two dozen patents

30:33.790 --> 30:35.374
that made him some money.

30:35.542 --> 30:38.377
He liquidated most of
his wealth a few years ago

30:38.545 --> 30:42.172
to buy some industrial
properties around airports,

30:42.340 --> 30:44.216
chemical plants,
raiI yards.

30:44.384 --> 30:46.885
- It doesn't add up.
- No, it's weird, right?

30:47.053 --> 30:48.512
Search 'em all, Sarah.
See what you find.

32:05.798 --> 32:07.674
Freeze!

32:09.010 --> 32:10.928
- Get down, go!
- On your knees!

32:12.096 --> 32:14.723
- Face down, face down!
- Pull him down and cuff him!

32:50.843 --> 32:54.054
Crazy men scare
the shit out of me.

32:54.222 --> 32:56.348
Is this guy a lawyer?

32:56.516 --> 32:57.975
No.

32:59.477 --> 33:01.770
He's an engineer.

33:01.938 --> 33:04.982
Nick, look at this.

33:42.311 --> 33:45.105
We have zero evidence.
Gonna need a confession.

33:45.273 --> 33:47.024
He give you any trouble
on the way in?

33:47.191 --> 33:48.400
No, nothing.

33:48.568 --> 33:51.319
He wasn't too happy when
we took his bracelet, though.

34:00.413 --> 34:02.789
- Can I help you?
- Package for the Rice family.

34:02.957 --> 34:05.876
Oh, yeah. Thanks.

34:07.587 --> 34:11.255
Mom, the video from my recital came.
Can we watch it?

34:11.424 --> 34:13.967
- Please?
- No, not you.

34:14.135 --> 34:16.719
No, please, we said we were
gonna wait for your father, remember?

34:16.888 --> 34:18.972
- Please?
- No, not now.

34:19.139 --> 34:21.224
Okay.

34:22.226 --> 34:24.770
Uh-huh, yes.

34:26.606 --> 34:28.774
Yes, absolutely.

34:48.168 --> 34:49.878
Mommy!

35:05.812 --> 35:09.106
Don't worry, he's just disarming
the guy, letting him feeI easy.

35:09.273 --> 35:13.485
What I'm about to tell you
I don't want anybody else to hear.

35:13.653 --> 35:16.404
As a prosecutor, I'm breaking
all the rules right now,

35:16.572 --> 35:19.282
and I don't give a damn
because I'm a father.

35:19.450 --> 35:21.368
I have a little girl.

35:21.536 --> 35:25.288
And what you did... bravo.

35:27.041 --> 35:31.461
The world is better
without Darby and Ames.

35:31.629 --> 35:36.133
You're not gonna see a tear shed
from me or anybody in my office.

35:39.887 --> 35:43.515
With that being said...

35:43.683 --> 35:45.892
I have a job to do.

35:48.104 --> 35:50.522
I'm gonna ask you some very simple
and direct questions.

35:50.690 --> 35:54.568
I suggest that you
answer them in the same fashion.

35:54.735 --> 35:56.736
Is your name Clyde Alexander Shelton?

35:57.738 --> 35:58.822
Yes, sir.

35:58.990 --> 36:00.740
And you've waived
your right to counsel, correct?

36:00.908 --> 36:04.703
- Yes, sir.
- You sure you want to do that?

36:04.871 --> 36:06.079
Yes.

36:06.247 --> 36:09.666
Did you murder Clarence Darby?

36:11.043 --> 36:13.628
I wanted him dead.

36:13.796 --> 36:15.463
He killed my wife and child.

36:15.631 --> 36:18.842
Rupert Ames-
did you murder him as well?

36:20.511 --> 36:22.387
Rupert Ames deserved to die.

36:22.555 --> 36:25.515
They both deserved to die.

36:25.683 --> 36:29.269
So you arranged
both of those murders?

36:30.521 --> 36:31.771
Yes, I planned it...

36:31.939 --> 36:35.775
in my head, over and over again.
It took me a long time.

36:38.821 --> 36:40.780
All right.

36:40.948 --> 36:43.116
I guess we're done here.

36:44.327 --> 36:45.869
Counselor?

36:47.622 --> 36:51.291
You might want to canceI
your 12:30 lunch with Judge Roberts.

36:52.293 --> 36:53.919
Excuse me?

36:54.086 --> 36:56.421
In fact, you might want to
cancel the rest of the week,

36:56.589 --> 36:59.299
'cause you're gonna be busy.
Sit down.

37:01.260 --> 37:03.678
We're done here.
We have your confession.

37:03.846 --> 37:06.181
Mmm. Oh, you do?

37:06.349 --> 37:07.933
On tape.

37:08.100 --> 37:10.936
See, in our profession,
we consider that a slam-dunk.

37:11.103 --> 37:13.855
Oh, really?
I don't think so. Let's think back.

37:14.023 --> 37:15.690
What did I say?

37:15.858 --> 37:18.860
That I wanted to kill
Clarence Darby?

37:19.028 --> 37:21.363
Yeah, sure.
What father wouldn't?

37:21.530 --> 37:24.157
That both Darby and Ames
deserved to die?

37:24.325 --> 37:25.951
I think most people
would agree with that.

37:26.118 --> 37:29.371
That I planned it over and over
again in my head?

37:29.538 --> 37:32.791
Yeah. Who wouldn't
fantasize about that?

37:32.959 --> 37:35.669
None of these are
an admission of guilt, Nick.

37:35.836 --> 37:38.546
- You might want to check the tape.
- We know you did it.

37:38.714 --> 37:42.050
Well, it's not what you know,
it's what you can prove in court.

37:42.218 --> 37:43.677
Didn't you tell me that once?

37:43.844 --> 37:45.178
The only problem with your theory

37:45.346 --> 37:47.472
is that Darby's body was
found on your property.

37:47.640 --> 37:50.809
One of my many properties-
an old abandoned warehouse, Nick.

37:50.977 --> 37:53.895
Junkies, they trespass there
all the time.

37:54.063 --> 37:56.147
Isn't Darby involved
in the drug trade?

37:56.315 --> 37:59.025
That's an unsavory world.
I bet you a jury would agree.

37:59.193 --> 38:02.237
Or perhaps someone was
trying to frame me.

38:02.405 --> 38:04.114
You know, Clyde,

38:04.282 --> 38:07.367
there's a lot of assholes in prison
that thought they were smarter than me.

38:07.535 --> 38:10.078
Let's stop fucking around.

38:10.246 --> 38:13.206
Nick, unless you have any
hard evidence,

38:13.374 --> 38:15.750
then why are we even here?
Why are we having this-

38:15.918 --> 38:18.336
- What do you want?
- -conversation?

38:20.172 --> 38:22.632
Well, that's easy.

38:22.800 --> 38:26.094
Now you're the one who
makes deals with murderers, yeah?

38:26.262 --> 38:28.471
So I've come to make mine.

38:28.639 --> 38:33.143
I will give you a confession,
a reaI confession.

38:33.311 --> 38:35.478
You just have to
give me something in return.

38:35.646 --> 38:38.815
Yeah, well, since you
are a murderer, what might that be?

38:39.817 --> 38:41.151
A bed.

38:43.863 --> 38:46.114
But a nice bed.

38:46.282 --> 38:48.700
I want a nice new one
for my cell.

38:48.868 --> 38:50.368
Very simple.

38:50.536 --> 38:53.079
You're gonna have to deal with that,
because the one I have is lumpy, Nick.

38:53.247 --> 38:55.290
It's making me crazy.

38:55.458 --> 38:58.043
Clyde, I think you've got me
confused with detail people.

38:58.210 --> 39:00.295
See, I don't deaI
with prison conditions.

39:00.463 --> 39:02.714
I believe those cots
are bolted into the cells.

39:02.882 --> 39:05.967
Well, that's what wrenches are for,
dumbass.

39:07.678 --> 39:09.387
You know, one of those new
Duxiana beds

39:09.555 --> 39:12.891
with the adjustable- you know,
adjustable lumbar support,

39:13.059 --> 39:14.392
- that's the one.
- I've seen the commercial.

39:14.560 --> 39:15.977
- That's the one I want.
- Those are nice.

39:16.145 --> 39:17.979
- 'Cause really-
- Comes on late at night.

39:18.147 --> 39:19.814
- And frankly I don't think-
- Two old people laying on the bed.

39:19.982 --> 39:21.399
- I'll be able to focus
on anything

39:21.567 --> 39:23.735
untiI I've had a good
revitalizing night's sleep

39:23.903 --> 39:26.154
in my therapeutic Duxiana bed.

39:26.322 --> 39:28.031
So that's the deal:

39:28.199 --> 39:31.743
you get me my bed,
you get your confession.

39:31.911 --> 39:34.746
Okay, let me think
about that for a second.

39:34.914 --> 39:37.040
How about...

39:37.208 --> 39:39.000
fuck no.

39:49.220 --> 39:51.012
Hey, what are you doing?

39:51.180 --> 39:53.306
- What do you mean?
- Why did you tell him no?

39:53.474 --> 39:56.601
A mattress? He doesn't make
those kinds of decisions.

39:56.769 --> 39:59.938
Take your ego out of it, Nick. Shelton's
- this case is shit.

40:00.106 --> 40:02.440
We need a confession.
And a mattress for a murder confession?

40:02.608 --> 40:04.818
- That's a pretty good deal.
- He's playing us, Jonas.

40:04.985 --> 40:06.486
Well, then we will play him.

40:06.654 --> 40:08.238
Nick?

40:08.406 --> 40:10.949
There's an urgent call from your office.
They say you're not answering your cell.

40:11.117 --> 40:13.952
I need to finish up here and then
I will be home as soon as I can.

40:14.120 --> 40:16.037
the things on this video-

40:16.205 --> 40:18.832
Nick, I have never seen
anything like it.

40:18.999 --> 40:20.333
Please come home.

40:20.501 --> 40:24.337
Listen, you need to calm down.
Tell her that it's not real...

40:24.505 --> 40:26.172
- Okay.
- ...and that I love her.

40:26.340 --> 40:27.382
Come home.
Come home soon, please.

40:27.550 --> 40:29.384
- Kelly, did you see his face?
- No.

40:29.552 --> 40:31.636
It was covered with something.
I couldn't see.

40:31.804 --> 40:34.806
Okay, baby, let me finish up here and
I'll come home as fast as I can, okay?

40:34.974 --> 40:36.850
Okay.

40:37.017 --> 40:40.103
This motherfucker sent a DVD to my house
of him killing Darby.

40:40.271 --> 40:43.064
- What?
- My daughter saw it.

40:44.817 --> 40:46.401
He recorded it?
We've got him.

40:46.569 --> 40:50.029
No no, he had on a mask.
We need that confession.

40:50.197 --> 40:52.323
You still want to bargain
with this man?

40:52.491 --> 40:54.701
The art of the possible, Warden.

40:54.869 --> 40:56.369
Make the deal.

40:58.789 --> 41:02.000
Hey, come on, man! Give us one!

41:14.054 --> 41:17.932
Back problems, Warden-
the worst.

41:18.100 --> 41:20.518
You got bigger problems than that.

41:20.686 --> 41:23.271
It's the have-nots in here, son.

41:23.439 --> 41:27.108
I don't know that I want
to be the one "have."

41:30.029 --> 41:32.363
Turn around.

41:36.243 --> 41:38.036
I don't think he likes me.

41:40.581 --> 41:42.415
Nice bed.

41:44.210 --> 41:46.252
Thank you.

41:46.420 --> 41:48.922
It's a single.

41:50.424 --> 41:53.635
I'd watch my fucking back
around here, you hear?

41:55.054 --> 41:56.429
In the cell, let's go.

42:00.476 --> 42:02.143
We can't put
Clyde Shelton anywhere-

42:02.311 --> 42:04.395
not in a job, not in a city,
not even the country.

42:04.563 --> 42:07.607
So I dug a little deeper and I found
something from his missing years:

42:07.775 --> 42:11.277
a couple of contract payments to Clyde
from the Department of Defense.

42:11.445 --> 42:14.113
- And his real estate?
- He bought nine properties

42:14.281 --> 42:16.199
under his own name,
then he transferred them

42:16.367 --> 42:17.534
to some corporation in Panama.

42:17.701 --> 42:19.577
We can't get to the addresses.

42:19.745 --> 42:21.162
A lack of reciprocity
is our problem.

42:21.330 --> 42:22.914
So I'm gonna circle
back to the farmhouse.

42:23.082 --> 42:26.292
That's a waste of time. He wanted us
to find it and find him there.

42:26.460 --> 42:28.670
It's the industrial stuff
that's curious.

42:28.837 --> 42:31.339
All right, I don't care what you
have to do and who you have to piss off.

42:31.507 --> 42:34.008
If we have to invade
Panama again, fine.

42:34.176 --> 42:36.678
Clyde is hiding those properties
for a reason. Find him.

42:36.845 --> 42:38.096
Got it.

42:50.192 --> 42:52.902
- Baby, you leave it cracked?
- Hmm? Yeah, I left it cracked.

42:53.070 --> 42:55.780
- Night light?
- Isn't she too old for a night light?

42:55.948 --> 42:58.199
Yeah, I left a night light.

42:58.367 --> 43:00.243
- Good.
- Look,

43:00.411 --> 43:02.245
I told her that
that video wasn't real.

43:02.413 --> 43:04.664
- Okay.
- It's some sort of horror film-

43:04.832 --> 43:06.332
something she shouldn't
be looking at anyway.

